properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 11 at 3:16AM EST until January 12 at 12:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, southwest winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 35 kt and seas 6 to 11 feet expected. For the
Small Craft Advisory, south winds 15 to 20 kt with gusts up to
25 kt and seas 3 to 6 feet expected.

* WHERE...The New Jersey and Delaware Atlantic coastal waters.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 6 PM this evening to noon
EST Sunday. For the Small Craft Advisory, until 6 PM EST this
evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
